-- L’Oreal Considers Angola, Cameroon Expansion, Bus. Report Says
-- B y   J a n a   M a r a i s
-- 2012-04-10T06:49:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-10/l-oreal-considers-angola-cameroon-expansion-bus-report-says.html
L’Oreal SA (OR)  expects the middle class
in Angola and Cameroon to expand sufficiently over the next
three years to warrant setting up operations there,  Business
Report  said, citing Geoff Skingsley, managing director for
Africa and the Middle East.  The company is planning to introduce Kiehls retail outlets
in South Africa as part of its strategy to win market share of
16 percent on the continent, the Johannesburg-based paper
reported Skingsley as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jana Marais in Johannesburg at 
 jmarais@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
